[4, "Make no mistake, this book is dense and complex. For those who have not read any others in this massive saga there is a seven page round-up and a lengthy prologue. But as one would expect from book three of any trilogy -- and this is also volume nine in the series, remember -- you should not, as they say, start here. You really do need to read, at least, the two preceding volumes to be able to follow the story in Destroyer of Worlds. But let's face it, few people would pick up a `last volume' and attempt to read it cold. We are assured that this is the last in the series; but although the doors close on an epic, there is just a tiniest chink left ajar...", [0, 0, 1, 3, 3], [0, 1, 8, 24, 26]]